Ext.data.JsonP['Titanium_Filesystem_File']({"tagname":"class","name":"Titanium.Filesystem.File","extends":"Titanium.Proxy","mixins":[],"alternateClassNames":[],"aliases":{},"singleton":false,"requires":[],"uses":[],"enum":null,"override":null,"inheritable":null,"inheritdoc":null,"meta":{"platform":["android 0.8","iphone 0.8","ipad 0.8","mobileweb 1.8","windowsphone 4.1.0"],"editurl":"https://github.com/appcelerator/titanium_mobile/edit/master/apidoc/Titanium/Filesystem/File.yml","description":["<p>Use the {@link Titanium.Filesystem#method-getFile} method to get a handle to a <code>File</code> object,\nwhich represents a given path.  There does not need to be an existing file or directory \ndoes not need to exist before <code>getFile</code> is called. If the file doesn't exist, and \nthe file path identifies a file in a writable directory, writing to the file \ncreates the file implicitly. </p>\n\n<p>See {@link Titanium.Filesystem} for constants identifying commonly-used device directories.</p>\n\n<p>Use the {@link Titanium.Filesystem.File#method-exists exists} method to test whether the file exists.</p>\n\n<p>A file object can point to an ordinary file, a directory or a symbolic link.\nUse {@link Titanium.Filesystem.File#method-createDirectory createDirectory} to create a directory.\nUse the {@link Titanium.Filesystem.File#method-getDirectoryListing getDirectoryListing} method to\nretrieve a list of the directory's contents.</p>\n\n<p>The <code>File</code> object doesn't provide methods for random access into the file.\nThe <code>read</code> method reads the file's entire contents into a <code>Blob</code> object.\nThe <code>write</code> method can either overwrite the entire file or append to an\nexisting file. </p>\n\n<p>For random access to a file, such as accessing a small portion of a larger file, \nyou can open a file as a {@link Titanium.Filesystem.FileStream FileStream} object. Use the \n{@link Titanium.Filesystem.File#method-open open} method to get a <code>FileStream</code> for an\nexisting <code>File</code> object, or use the {@link Titanium.Filesystem#method-openStream} method \nto get a <code>FileStream</code> directly without calling <code>getFile</code> first.</p>\n\n<p>The {@link Titanium.Filesystem} module defines a number of properties and methods related to \nfilesystem access, including properties that specify paths for application-specific \ndirectories, and methods for creating temporary files and directories.</p>\n\n<p>On Android, files may be stored on external storage (that is, removable media such as \nSD Cards).</p>\n\n<p>Note that once created with <code>getFile</code>, the path associated with a file object is\nimmutable. If you move the underlying file using {@link Titanium.Filesystem.File#method-move move} \nor {@link Titanium.Filesystem.File#method-rename rename}, you can no longer access it with the \noriginal <code>File</code> object. You must use <code>getFile</code> to get a handle to the new path.</p>\n\n<h4>Resource Files</h4>\n\n<p>The <code>Resources</code> directory and all the files in it are read-only. On Android, resource\nfiles are stored in the resource bundle and do not have all of the properties of\nnormal files. In particular, they do not have creation or modification timestamps.</p> \n<h3>Examples</h3>\n<h4>Reading a File</h4>\n<p>Data files shipped with the application are stored in the resources directory.</p>\n\n<p>This example reads string data from a text file.</p>\n\n<pre><code>// resourcesDirectory is actually the default location, so the first \n// argument could be omitted here.\nfile = Ti.Filesystem.getFile(Ti.Filesystem.resourcesDirectory, \"textfile.txt\");\nvar blob = file.read();\nvar readText = blob.text;\n// dispose of file handle &amp; blob.\nfile = null;\nblob = null;\n</code></pre><h4>Creating a Subdirectory</h4>\n<p>Files that the application writes to need to be stored outside of the \nresources directory, since that directory is read-only.</p>\n\n<p>This example creates a subdirectory to store downloaded images.\nThe example assumes that two variables are defined elsewhere in the code:\nmyImageID, a string containing some kind of ID for the downloaded image, \nand myImageData, a <code>Blob</code> containing JPEG image data.</p>\n\n<pre><code>var imageDir = Ti.Filesystem.getFile(Ti.Filesystem.applicationDataDirectory,            \n    'downloaded_images');\nif (! imageDir.exists()) {\n    imageDir.createDirectory();\n}\n\n// .resolve() provides the resolved native path for the directory.\nvar imageFile  = Ti.Filesystem.getFile(imageDir.resolve(), myImageID + '.jpg');\nTi.API.info(\"ImageFile path is: \" + imageFile.resolve());\nif (imageFile.write(myImageData)===false) {\n    // handle write error\n}\n// dispose of file handles\nimageFile = null;\nimageDir = null;\n</code></pre>"]},"private":null,"id":"class-Titanium.Filesystem.File","members":{"cfg":[],"property":[{"name":"apiName","tagname":"property","owner":"Titanium.Proxy","meta":{"readonly":true,"description":["<p>The value of this property is the fully qualified name of the API. For example, {@link Titanium.UI.Button Button}\nreturns <code>Ti.UI.Button</code>.</p>"],"platform":["android 3.2.0","iphone 3.2.0","ipad 3.2.0","mobileweb 3.2.0","windowsphone 4.1.0"]},"id":"property-apiName"},{"name":"bubbleParent","tagname":"property","owner":"Titanium.Proxy","meta":{"description":["<p>Some proxies (most commonly views) have a relationship to other proxies, often\nestablished by the add() method. For example, for a button added to a window, a\nclick event on the button would bubble up to the window. Other common parents are\ntable sections to their rows, table views to their sections, and scrollable views\nto their views. Set this property to false to disable the bubbling to the proxy's parent.</p>"],"platform":["android 3.0.0","iphone 3.0.0","ipad 3.0.0","windowsphone 4.1.0"]},"id":"property-bubbleParent"},{"name":"executable","tagname":"property","owner":"Titanium.Filesystem.File","meta":{"readonly":true,"description":["<p>On iOS, Mobile Web, this property exists but is always <code>false</code>.</p>"],"platform":["android 0.8","iphone 0.8","ipad 0.8","mobileweb 1.8"]},"id":"property-executable"},{"name":"hidden","tagname":"property","owner":"Titanium.Filesystem.File","meta":{"description":["<p>On iOS, Mobile Web, this property exists but is always <code>false</code>.</p>"]},"id":"property-hidden"},{"name":"lifecycleContainer","tagname":"property","owner":"Titanium.Proxy","meta":{"description":["<p>If this property is set to a Window or TabGroup, then the corresponding Activity lifecycle event callbacks\nwill also be called on the proxy. Proxies that require the activity lifecycle will need this property set\nto the appropriate containing Window or TabGroup.</p>"],"platform":["android 3.6.0","windowsphone 4.1.0"]},"id":"property-lifecycleContainer"},{"name":"name","tagname":"property","owner":"Titanium.Filesystem.File","meta":{"readonly":true},"id":"property-name"},{"name":"nativePath","tagname":"property","owner":"Titanium.Filesystem.File","meta":{"readonly":true,"description":["<p>On iOS, use the {@link Titanium.Filesystem.File#method-resolve resolve} \nmethod to obtain a plain file path for use with native modules.</p>"]},"id":"property-nativePath"},{"name":"parent","tagname":"property","owner":"Titanium.Filesystem.File","meta":{"readonly":true,"platform":["android 0.8","mobileweb 1.8","windowsphone 4.1.0"]},"id":"property-parent"},{"name":"readonly","tagname":"property","owner":"Titanium.Filesystem.File","meta":{"readonly":true,"description":["<p>On Mobile Web, this property exists but is always <code>true</code> for files in the resources directory\nand <code>false</code> for application data and temporary files.</p>"],"platform":["android 0.8","mobileweb 1.8","windowsphone 4.1.0"]},"id":"property-readonly"},{"name":"remoteBackup","tagname":"property","owner":"Titanium.Filesystem.File","meta":{"description":["<p>Some apps may be rejected by Apple for backing up specific files; if this\nis the case, ensure that this value is set to <code>false</code> for them. This\nvalue should only need to be set once by your app, but setting it\nmultiple times will not cause problems. For files distributed with your\napp, this will need to be set on boot. This flag will only affect iOS\nversions 5.0.1 and later, but is safe to set on earlier versions.</p>\n\n<p>Note that setting this property to <code>false</code> will also prevent the\nfile identified by this object from being backed up to iTunes.</p>"],"platform":["iphone 1.8.0","ipad 1.8.0"]},"id":"property-remoteBackup"},{"name":"size","tagname":"property","owner":"Titanium.Filesystem.File","meta":{"readonly":true},"id":"property-size"},{"name":"symbolicLink","tagname":"property","owner":"Titanium.Filesystem.File","meta":{"readonly":true,"description":["<p>On Mobile Web, this property exists but is always <code>false</code>.</p>"],"platform":["android 0.8","iphone 0.8","ipad 0.8","mobileweb 1.8"]},"id":"property-symbolicLink"},{"name":"writable","tagname":"property","owner":"Titanium.Filesystem.File","meta":{"readonly":true},"id":"property-writable"},{"name":"writeable","tagname":"property","owner":"Titanium.Filesystem.File","meta":{"readonly":true,"removed":{"version":"6.0.0","text":"Use [writable](Titanium.Filesystem.File.writable) instead."},"platform":["iphone 0.8","ipad 0.8"]},"id":"property-writeable"}],"method":[{"name":"addEventListener","tagname":"method","owner":"Titanium.Proxy","meta":{},"id":"method-addEventListener"},{"name":"append","tagname":"method","owner":"Titanium.Filesystem.File","meta":{"description":["<p>Data to append can be specified as a String, <code>Blob</code>, or <code>File</code>.</p>\n\n<p>If the <code>data</code> argument is a <code>File</code> object, the file's contents\nare appended to this file.</p>\n\n<p>Returns <code>true</code> if the operation succeeds.</p>"],"platform":["iphone 0.8","ipad 0.8","mobileweb 1.8","windowsphone 4.1.0"]},"id":"method-append"},{"name":"applyProperties","tagname":"method","owner":"Titanium.Proxy","meta":{"description":["<p>Properties are supplied as a dictionary. Each key-value pair in the object is applied to the proxy such that\nmyproxy[key] = value.</p>"],"platform":["android 3.0.0","iphone 3.0.0","ipad 3.0.0","mobileweb 3.0.0","windowsphone 4.1.0"]},"id":"method-applyProperties"},{"name":"copy","tagname":"method","owner":"Titanium.Filesystem.File","meta":{"description":["<p>Returns <code>true</code> if the copy succeeds.</p>"],"platform":["android 0.8","mobileweb 1.8","windowsphone 4.1.0"]},"id":"method-copy"},{"name":"createDirectory","tagname":"method","owner":"Titanium.Filesystem.File","meta":{"description":["<p>Returns <code>true</code> if the directory was created successfully.</p>"]},"id":"method-createDirectory"},{"name":"createFile","tagname":"method","owner":"Titanium.Filesystem.File","meta":{"description":["<p>Note that if you write to a file that doesn't exist, the file is created automatically,\nso it is not necessary to call this method unless you want to explicitly create the file\n(for example, to create an empty file).</p>\n\n<p>Returns <code>true</code> if the file was created successfully. Returns <code>false</code> if the \nfile already exists, or if the file couldn't be created for some other reason.</p>"],"platform":["iphone 0.8","ipad 0.8","mobileweb 1.8","windowsphone 4.1.0"]},"id":"method-createFile"},{"name":"createTimestamp","tagname":"method","owner":"Titanium.Filesystem.File","meta":{"description":["<p>On Android, returns 0 for resource files.</p>"]},"id":"method-createTimestamp"},{"name":"deleteDirectory","tagname":"method","owner":"Titanium.Filesystem.File","meta":{"description":["<p>Returns <code>true</code> if the operation was successful. Does nothing if the file\nobject does not identify a directory.</p>"]},"id":"method-deleteDirectory"},{"name":"deleteFile","tagname":"method","owner":"Titanium.Filesystem.File","meta":{"description":["<p>Returns <code>true</code> if the operation was successful.</p>"]},"id":"method-deleteFile"},{"name":"exists","tagname":"method","owner":"Titanium.Filesystem.File","meta":{},"id":"method-exists"},{"name":"extension","tagname":"method","owner":"Titanium.Filesystem.File","meta":{},"id":"method-extension"},{"name":"fireEvent","tagname":"method","owner":"Titanium.Proxy","meta":{},"id":"method-fireEvent"},{"name":"getApiName","tagname":"method","owner":"Titanium.Proxy","meta":{"platform":["android 3.2.0","iphone 3.2.0","ipad 3.2.0","mobileweb 3.2.0","windowsphone 4.1.0"]},"id":"method-getApiName"},{"name":"getBubbleParent","tagname":"method","owner":"Titanium.Proxy","meta":{"platform":["android 3.0.0","iphone 3.0.0","ipad 3.0.0","windowsphone 4.1.0"]},"id":"method-getBubbleParent"},{"name":"getDirectoryListing","tagname":"method","owner":"Titanium.Filesystem.File","meta":{},"id":"method-getDirectoryListing"},{"name":"getExecutable","tagname":"method","owner":"Titanium.Filesystem.File","meta":{"platform":["android 0.8","iphone 0.8","ipad 0.8","mobileweb 1.8"]},"id":"method-getExecutable"},{"name":"getHidden","tagname":"method","owner":"Titanium.Filesystem.File","meta":{},"id":"method-getHidden"},{"name":"getLifecycleContainer","tagname":"method","owner":"Titanium.Proxy","meta":{"platform":["android 3.6.0","windowsphone 4.1.0"]},"id":"method-getLifecycleContainer"},{"name":"getName","tagname":"method","owner":"Titanium.Filesystem.File","meta":{},"id":"method-getName"},{"name":"getNativePath","tagname":"method","owner":"Titanium.Filesystem.File","meta":{},"id":"method-getNativePath"},{"name":"getParent","tagname":"method","owner":"Titanium.Filesystem.File","meta":{"platform":["android 0.8","mobileweb 1.8","windowsphone 4.1.0"]},"id":"method-getParent"},{"name":"getProtectionKey","tagname":"method","owner":"Titanium.Filesystem.File","meta":{"platform":["iphone 4.1.0","ipad 4.1.0"]},"id":"method-getProtectionKey"},{"name":"getReadonly","tagname":"method","owner":"Titanium.Filesystem.File","meta":{"platform":["android 0.8","mobileweb 1.8","windowsphone 4.1.0"]},"id":"method-getReadonly"},{"name":"getRemoteBackup","tagname":"method","owner":"Titanium.Filesystem.File","meta":{"platform":["iphone 1.8.0","ipad 1.8.0"]},"id":"method-getRemoteBackup"},{"name":"getSize","tagname":"method","owner":"Titanium.Filesystem.File","meta":{},"id":"method-getSize"},{"name":"getSymbolicLink","tagname":"method","owner":"Titanium.Filesystem.File","meta":{"platform":["android 0.8","iphone 0.8","ipad 0.8","mobileweb 1.8"]},"id":"method-getSymbolicLink"},{"name":"getWritable","tagname":"method","owner":"Titanium.Filesystem.File","meta":{},"id":"method-getWritable"},{"name":"getWriteable","tagname":"method","owner":"Titanium.Filesystem.File","meta":{"removed":{"version":"6.0.0","text":"Use [writable](Titanium.Filesystem.File.writable) instead."},"platform":["iphone 0.8","ipad 0.8"]},"id":"method-getWriteable"},{"name":"isDirectory","tagname":"method","owner":"Titanium.Filesystem.File","meta":{"platform":["android 0.8","iphone 3.1.0","ipad 3.1.0","mobileweb 1.8","windowsphone 4.1.0"]},"id":"method-isDirectory"},{"name":"isFile","tagname":"method","owner":"Titanium.Filesystem.File","meta":{"platform":["android 0.8","iphone 3.1.0","ipad 3.1.0","mobileweb 1.8","windowsphone 4.1.0"]},"id":"method-isFile"},{"name":"modificationTimestamp","tagname":"method","owner":"Titanium.Filesystem.File","meta":{"description":["<p>On Android, returns 0 for resource files.</p>"]},"id":"method-modificationTimestamp"},{"name":"move","tagname":"method","owner":"Titanium.Filesystem.File","meta":{"description":["<p>Note that this method moves the stored file, but doesn't update this \nfile object to point to the new path. To access the file after moving it,\nyou must call {@link Titanium.Filesystem#method-getFile getFile} using the destination\npath to obtain a new file handle.</p>"]},"id":"method-move"},{"name":"open","tagname":"method","owner":"Titanium.Filesystem.File","meta":{"description":["<p>You can open the file for reading, writing, or appending by specifying one of the \n<code>MODE</code> constants from {@link Titanium.Filesystem}:\n{@link Titanium.Filesystem#property-MODE_READ MODE_READ}, {@link Titanium.Filesystem#property-MODE_WRITE MODE_WRITE}, \nor {@link Titanium.Filesystem#property-MODE_APPEND MODE_APPEND}.</p>\n\n<p>The <code>FileStream</code> object returned by this call can be used to read from, write to, or \nappend to the file, depending on what mode the file is opened in.</p>"]},"id":"method-open"},{"name":"read","tagname":"method","owner":"Titanium.Filesystem.File","meta":{},"id":"method-read"},{"name":"removeEventListener","tagname":"method","owner":"Titanium.Proxy","meta":{"description":["<p>Multiple listeners can be registered for the same event, so the \n<code>callback</code> parameter is used to determine which listener to remove. </p>\n\n<p>When adding a listener, you must save a reference to the callback function\nin order to remove the listener later:</p>\n\n<pre><code>var listener = function() { Ti.API.info(\"Event listener called.\"); }\nwindow.addEventListener('click', listener);\n</code></pre>\n\n<p>To remove the listener, pass in a reference to the callback function:</p>\n\n<pre><code>window.removeEventListener('click', listener);\n</code></pre>"]},"id":"method-removeEventListener"},{"name":"rename","tagname":"method","owner":"Titanium.Filesystem.File","meta":{"description":["<p>Returns <code>true</code> if the file was successfully renamed.</p>\n\n<p>Fails if the destination is in a different directory than the current file.\nUse {@link Titanium.Filesystem.File#method-move move} to move a file to a different directory.</p>\n\n<p>Note that this method renames the stored file, but doesn't update this \nfile object to point to the new path. To access the file after renaming it,\nyou must call {@link Titanium.Filesystem#method-getFile getFile} using the destination\npath to obtain a new file handle.</p>"]},"id":"method-rename"},{"name":"resolve","tagname":"method","owner":"Titanium.Filesystem.File","meta":{"description":["<p>On iOS, the path returned by this method is a plain file path, not a URL. It is suitable\nfor use in native modules that need to access the file using native APIs.</p>\n\n<p>On Android, the return value of <code>resolve</code> is a <code>file://</code> URL, identical to the\n{@link Titanium.Filesystem.File#property-nativePath nativePath} property.</p>"]},"id":"method-resolve"},{"name":"setBubbleParent","tagname":"method","owner":"Titanium.Proxy","meta":{"platform":["android 3.0.0","iphone 3.0.0","ipad 3.0.0","windowsphone 4.1.0"]},"id":"method-setBubbleParent"},{"name":"setHidden","tagname":"method","owner":"Titanium.Filesystem.File","meta":{},"id":"method-setHidden"},{"name":"setLifecycleContainer","tagname":"method","owner":"Titanium.Proxy","meta":{"platform":["android 3.6.0","windowsphone 4.1.0"]},"id":"method-setLifecycleContainer"},{"name":"setProtectionKey","tagname":"method","owner":"Titanium.Filesystem.File","meta":{"description":["<p>Returns <code>true</code> if successfully set. Returns <code>false</code> if failed.</p>"],"platform":["iphone 4.1.0","ipad 4.1.0"]},"id":"method-setProtectionKey"},{"name":"setRemoteBackup","tagname":"method","owner":"Titanium.Filesystem.File","meta":{"platform":["iphone 1.8.0","ipad 1.8.0"]},"id":"method-setRemoteBackup"},{"name":"spaceAvailable","tagname":"method","owner":"Titanium.Filesystem.File","meta":{"description":["<p>Free space is returned in bytes.</p>"]},"id":"method-spaceAvailable"},{"name":"write","tagname":"method","owner":"Titanium.Filesystem.File","meta":{"description":["<p>If the <code>append</code> parameter is <code>false</code> or not specified, any existing data in \nthe file is overwritten. </p>\n\n<p>If <code>append</code> is <code>true</code>, the specified data is appended to the end of the file.</p>"]},"id":"method-write"}],"event":[],"css_var":[],"css_mixin":[]},"linenr":77672,"files":[{"filename":"titanium.js","href":"titanium.html#Titanium-Filesystem-File"}],"html_meta":{"platform":"<ul class='platforms'><li class='platform-android'\n        title='Android'>0.8</li><li class='platform-iphone'\n        title='iPhone'>0.8</li><li class='platform-ipad'\n        title='iPad'>0.8</li><li class='platform-mobileweb'\n        title='Mobile Web'>1.8</li><li class='platform-windowsphone'\n        title='Window Phone'>4.1.0</li></ul>","editurl":null,"description":"<p><p>Use the <a href=\"#!/api/Titanium.Filesystem-method-getFile\" rel=\"Titanium.Filesystem-method-getFile\" class=\"docClass\">Titanium.Filesystem.getFile</a> method to get a handle to a <code>File</code> object,\nwhich represents a given path.  There does not need to be an existing file or directory \ndoes not need to exist before <code>getFile</code> is called. If the file doesn't exist, and \nthe file path identifies a file in a writable directory, writing to the file \ncreates the file implicitly. </p>\n\n\n\n\n<p>See <a href=\"#!/api/Titanium.Filesystem\" rel=\"Titanium.Filesystem\" class=\"docClass\">Titanium.Filesystem</a> for constants identifying commonly-used device directories.</p>\n\n\n\n\n<p>Use the <a href=\"#!/api/Titanium.Filesystem.File-method-exists\" rel=\"Titanium.Filesystem.File-method-exists\" class=\"docClass\">exists</a> method to test whether the file exists.</p>\n\n\n\n\n<p>A file object can point to an ordinary file, a directory or a symbolic link.\nUse <a href=\"#!/api/Titanium.Filesystem.File-method-createDirectory\" rel=\"Titanium.Filesystem.File-method-createDirectory\" class=\"docClass\">createDirectory</a> to create a directory.\nUse the <a href=\"#!/api/Titanium.Filesystem.File-method-getDirectoryListing\" rel=\"Titanium.Filesystem.File-method-getDirectoryListing\" class=\"docClass\">getDirectoryListing</a> method to\nretrieve a list of the directory's contents.</p>\n\n\n\n\n<p>The <code>File</code> object doesn't provide methods for random access into the file.\nThe <code>read</code> method reads the file's entire contents into a <code>Blob</code> object.\nThe <code>write</code> method can either overwrite the entire file or append to an\nexisting file. </p>\n\n\n\n\n<p>For random access to a file, such as accessing a small portion of a larger file, \nyou can open a file as a <a href=\"#!/api/Titanium.Filesystem.FileStream\" rel=\"Titanium.Filesystem.FileStream\" class=\"docClass\">FileStream</a> object. Use the \n<a href=\"#!/api/Titanium.Filesystem.File-method-open\" rel=\"Titanium.Filesystem.File-method-open\" class=\"docClass\">open</a> method to get a <code>FileStream</code> for an\nexisting <code>File</code> object, or use the <a href=\"#!/api/Titanium.Filesystem-method-openStream\" rel=\"Titanium.Filesystem-method-openStream\" class=\"docClass\">Titanium.Filesystem.openStream</a> method \nto get a <code>FileStream</code> directly without calling <code>getFile</code> first.</p>\n\n\n\n\n<p>The <a href=\"#!/api/Titanium.Filesystem\" rel=\"Titanium.Filesystem\" class=\"docClass\">Titanium.Filesystem</a> module defines a number of properties and methods related to \nfilesystem access, including properties that specify paths for application-specific \ndirectories, and methods for creating temporary files and directories.</p>\n\n\n\n\n<p>On Android, files may be stored on external storage (that is, removable media such as \nSD Cards).</p>\n\n\n\n\n<p>Note that once created with <code>getFile</code>, the path associated with a file object is\nimmutable. If you move the underlying file using <a href=\"#!/api/Titanium.Filesystem.File-method-move\" rel=\"Titanium.Filesystem.File-method-move\" class=\"docClass\">move</a> \nor <a href=\"#!/api/Titanium.Filesystem.File-method-rename\" rel=\"Titanium.Filesystem.File-method-rename\" class=\"docClass\">rename</a>, you can no longer access it with the \noriginal <code>File</code> object. You must use <code>getFile</code> to get a handle to the new path.</p>\n\n\n\n\n<h4>Resource Files</h4>\n\n\n\n\n<p>The <code>Resources</code> directory and all the files in it are read-only. On Android, resource\nfiles are stored in the resource bundle and do not have all of the properties of\nnormal files. In particular, they do not have creation or modification timestamps.</p>\n\n\n<p></p>\n\n<h3>Examples</h3>\n\n\n<h4>Reading a File</h4>\n\n\n<p>Data files shipped with the application are stored in the resources directory.</p>\n\n\n\n\n<p>This example reads string data from a text file.</p>\n\n\n\n\n<pre><code>// resourcesDirectory is actually the default location, so the first \n// argument could be omitted here.\nfile = Ti.Filesystem.getFile(Ti.Filesystem.resourcesDirectory, \"textfile.txt\");\nvar blob = file.read();\nvar readText = blob.text;\n// dispose of file handle &amp; blob.\nfile = null;\nblob = null;\n</code></pre>\n\n\n<h4>Creating a Subdirectory</h4>\n\n\n<p>Files that the application writes to need to be stored outside of the \nresources directory, since that directory is read-only.</p>\n\n\n\n\n<p>This example creates a subdirectory to store downloaded images.\nThe example assumes that two variables are defined elsewhere in the code:\nmyImageID, a string containing some kind of ID for the downloaded image, \nand myImageData, a <code>Blob</code> containing JPEG image data.</p>\n\n\n\n\n<pre><code>var imageDir = Ti.Filesystem.getFile(Ti.Filesystem.applicationDataDirectory,            \n    'downloaded_images');\nif (! imageDir.exists()) {\n    imageDir.createDirectory();\n}\n\n// .resolve() provides the resolved native path for the directory.\nvar imageFile  = Ti.Filesystem.getFile(imageDir.resolve(), myImageID + '.jpg');\nTi.API.info(\"ImageFile path is: \" + imageFile.resolve());\nif (imageFile.write(myImageData)===false) {\n    // handle write error\n}\n// dispose of file handles\nimageFile = null;\nimageDir = null;\n</code></pre>\n\n</p>"},"statics":{"cfg":[],"property":[],"method":[],"event":[],"css_var":[],"css_mixin":[]},"component":false,"superclasses":["Titanium.Proxy","Titanium.Filesystem.File"],"subclasses":[],"mixedInto":[],"parentMixins":[],"html":"<div><div class='sidebar'><ul class=\"sidebar-platforms\"><li class='platform-android' title='Android since Titanium SDK 0.8'>Android 0.8</li><li class='platform-iphone' title='iPhone since Titanium SDK 0.8'>iPhone 0.8</li><li class='platform-ipad' title='iPad since Titanium SDK 0.8'>iPad 0.8</li><li class='platform-mobileweb' title='Mobile Web since Titanium SDK 1.8'>Mobile Web 1.8</li><li class='platform-windowsphone' title='Windows Phone since Titanium SDK 4.1.0'>Windows Phone 4.1.0</li></ul></div><div class='hierarchy'><div class='classes'><div class='subclass'><a href='#!/api/Titanium.Proxy' rel='Titanium.Proxy' class='docClass'>Titanium.Proxy</a></div><div class='subclass'> &gt; <strong>Titanium.Filesystem.File</strong></div></div></div><div class='doc-contents'><p>Object representing a path to a file or directory in the device's persistent storage.</p>\n\n<p><p>Use the <a href=\"#!/api/Titanium.Filesystem-method-getFile\" rel=\"Titanium.Filesystem-method-getFile\" class=\"docClass\">Titanium.Filesystem.getFile</a> method to get a handle to a <code>File</code> object,\nwhich represents a given path.  There does not need to be an existing file or directory \ndoes not need to exist before <code>getFile</code> is called. If the file doesn't exist, and \nthe file path identifies a file in a writable directory, writing to the file \ncreates the file implicitly. </p>\n\n\n\n\n<p>See <a href=\"#!/api/Titanium.Filesystem\" rel=\"Titanium.Filesystem\" class=\"docClass\">Titanium.Filesystem</a> for constants identifying commonly-used device directories.</p>\n\n\n\n\n<p>Use the <a href=\"#!/api/Titanium.Filesystem.File-method-exists\" rel=\"Titanium.Filesystem.File-method-exists\" class=\"docClass\">exists</a> method to test whether the file exists.</p>\n\n\n\n\n<p>A file object can point to an ordinary file, a directory or a symbolic link.\nUse <a href=\"#!/api/Titanium.Filesystem.File-method-createDirectory\" rel=\"Titanium.Filesystem.File-method-createDirectory\" class=\"docClass\">createDirectory</a> to create a directory.\nUse the <a href=\"#!/api/Titanium.Filesystem.File-method-getDirectoryListing\" rel=\"Titanium.Filesystem.File-method-getDirectoryListing\" class=\"docClass\">getDirectoryListing</a> method to\nretrieve a list of the directory's contents.</p>\n\n\n\n\n<p>The <code>File</code> object doesn't provide methods for random access into the file.\nThe <code>read</code> method reads the file's entire contents into a <code>Blob</code> object.\nThe <code>write</code> method can either overwrite the entire file or append to an\nexisting file. </p>\n\n\n\n\n<p>For random access to a file, such as accessing a small portion of a larger file, \nyou can open a file as a <a href=\"#!/api/Titanium.Filesystem.FileStream\" rel=\"Titanium.Filesystem.FileStream\" class=\"docClass\">FileStream</a> object. Use the \n<a href=\"#!/api/Titanium.Filesystem.File-method-open\" rel=\"Titanium.Filesystem.File-method-open\" class=\"docClass\">open</a> method to get a <code>FileStream</code> for an\nexisting <code>File</code> object, or use the <a href=\"#!/api/Titanium.Filesystem-method-openStream\" rel=\"Titanium.Filesystem-method-openStream\" class=\"docClass\">Titanium.Filesystem.openStream</a> method \nto get a <code>FileStream</code> directly without calling <code>getFile</code> first.</p>\n\n\n\n\n<p>The <a href=\"#!/api/Titanium.Filesystem\" rel=\"Titanium.Filesystem\" class=\"docClass\">Titanium.Filesystem</a> module defines a number of properties and methods related to \nfilesystem access, including properties that specify paths for application-specific \ndirectories, and methods for creating temporary files and directories.</p>\n\n\n\n\n<p>On Android, files may be stored on external storage (that is, removable media such as \nSD Cards).</p>\n\n\n\n\n<p>Note that once created with <code>getFile</code>, the path associated with a file object is\nimmutable. If you move the underlying file using <a href=\"#!/api/Titanium.Filesystem.File-method-move\" rel=\"Titanium.Filesystem.File-method-move\" class=\"docClass\">move</a> \nor <a href=\"#!/api/Titanium.Filesystem.File-method-rename\" rel=\"Titanium.Filesystem.File-method-rename\" class=\"docClass\">rename</a>, you can no longer access it with the \noriginal <code>File</code> object. You must use <code>getFile</code> to get a handle to the new path.</p>\n\n\n\n\n<h4>Resource Files</h4>\n\n\n\n\n<p>The <code>Resources</code> directory and all the files in it are read-only. On Android, resource\nfiles are stored in the resource bundle and do not have all of the properties of\nnormal files. In particular, they do not have creation or modification timestamps.</p>\n\n\n<p></p>\n\n<h3>Examples</h3>\n\n\n<h4>Reading a File</h4>\n\n\n<p>Data files shipped with the application are stored in the resources directory.</p>\n\n\n\n\n<p>This example reads string data from a text file.</p>\n\n\n\n\n<pre><code>// resourcesDirectory is actually the default location, so the first \n// argument could be omitted here.\nfile = Ti.Filesystem.getFile(Ti.Filesystem.resourcesDirectory, \"textfile.txt\");\nvar blob = file.read();\nvar readText = blob.text;\n// dispose of file handle &amp; blob.\nfile = null;\nblob = null;\n</code></pre>\n\n\n<h4>Creating a Subdirectory</h4>\n\n\n<p>Files that the application writes to need to be stored outside of the \nresources directory, since that directory is read-only.</p>\n\n\n\n\n<p>This example creates a subdirectory to store downloaded images.\nThe example assumes that two variables are defined elsewhere in the code:\nmyImageID, a string containing some kind of ID for the downloaded image, \nand myImageData, a <code>Blob</code> containing JPEG image data.</p>\n\n\n\n\n<pre><code>var imageDir = Ti.Filesystem.getFile(Ti.Filesystem.applicationDataDirectory,            \n    'downloaded_images');\nif (! imageDir.exists()) {\n    imageDir.createDirectory();\n}\n\n// .resolve() provides the resolved native path for the directory.\nvar imageFile  = Ti.Filesystem.getFile(imageDir.resolve(), myImageID + '.jpg');\nTi.API.info(\"ImageFile path is: \" + imageFile.resolve());\nif (imageFile.write(myImageData)===false) {\n    // handle write error\n}\n// dispose of file handles\nimageFile = null;\nimageDir = null;\n</code></pre>\n\n</p><ul class='platforms'><li class='platform-android'\n        title='Android'>0.8</li><li class='platform-iphone'\n        title='iPhone'>0.8</li><li class='platform-ipad'\n        title='iPad'>0.8</li><li class='platform-mobileweb'\n        title='Mobile Web'>1.8</li><li class='platform-windowsphone'\n        title='Window Phone'>4.1.0</li></ul></div><div class='members'><div class='members-section'><div class='definedBy'>Defined By</div><h3 class='members-title icon-property'>Properties</h3><div class='subsection'><div id='property-apiName' class='member first-child inherited'><a href='#' class='side expandable'><span>&nbsp;</span></a><div class='title'><div class='meta'><a href='#!/api/Titanium.Proxy' rel='Titanium.Proxy' class='defined-in docClass'>Titanium.Proxy</a></div><a href='#!/api/Titanium.Proxy-property-apiName' class='name not-expandable'>apiName</a><span> : String</span><strong class='readonly signature' >readonly</strong></div><div class='description'><div class='short'><p>The name of the API that this proxy corresponds to.</p>\n\n</div><div class='long'><p>The name of the API that this proxy corresponds to.</p>\n\n<p><p>The value of this property is the fully qualified name of the API. For example, <a href=\"#!/api/Titanium.UI.Button\" rel=\"Titanium.UI.Button\" class=\"docClass\">Button</a>\nreturns <code>Ti.UI.Button</code>.</p>\n\n</p><ul class='platforms'><li class='platform-android'\n        title='Android'>3.2.0</li><li class='platform-iphone'\n        title='iPhone'>3.2.0</li><li class='platform-ipad'\n        title='iPad'>3.2.0</li><li class='platform-mobileweb'\n        title='Mobile Web'>3.2.0</li><li class='platform-windowsphone'\n        title='Window Phone'>4.1.0</li></ul></div></div></div><div id='property-bubbleParent' class='member  inherited'><a href='#' class='side expandable'><span>&nbsp;</span></a><div class='title'><div class='meta'><a href='#!/api/Titanium.Proxy' rel='Titanium.Proxy' class='defined-in docClass'>Titanium.Proxy</a></div><a href='#!/api/Titanium.Proxy-property-bubbleParent' class='name expandable'>bubbleParent</a><span> : Boolean</span></div><div class='description'><div class='short'>Indicates if the proxy will bubble an event to its parent. ...</div><div class='long'><p>Indicates if the proxy will bubble an event to its parent.</p>\n\n<p><p>Some proxies (most commonly views) have a relationship to other proxies, often\nestablished by the add() method. For example, for a button added to a window, a\nclick event on the button would bubble up to the window. Other common parents are\ntable sections to their rows, table views to their sections, and scrollable views\nto their views. Set this property to false to disable the bubbling to the proxy's parent.</p>\n\n</p><p>Default: true</p><ul class='platforms'><li class='platform-android'\n        title='Android'>3.0.0</li><li class='platform-iphone'\n        title='iPhone'>3.0.0</li><li class='platform-ipad'\n        title='iPad'>3.0.0</li><li class='platform-windowsphone'\n        title='Window Phone'>4.1.0</li></ul></div></div></div><div id='property-executable' class='member  not-inherited'><a href='#' class='side expandable'><span>&nbsp;</span></a><div class='title'><div class='meta'><span class='defined-in' rel='Titanium.Filesystem.File'>Titanium.Filesystem.File</span></div><a href='#!/api/Titanium.Filesystem.File-property-executable' class='name not-expandable'>executable</a><span> : Boolean</span><strong class='readonly signature' >readonly</strong></div><div class='description'><div class='short'><p><code>true</code> if the file is executable.</p>\n\n</div><div class='long'><p><code>true</code> if the file is executable.</p>\n\n<p><p>On iOS, Mobile Web, this property exists but is always <code>false</code>.</p>\n\n</p><ul class='platforms'><li class='platform-android'\n        title='Android'>0.8</li><li class='platform-iphone'\n        title='iPhone'>0.8</li><li class='platform-ipad'\n        title='iPad'>0.8</li><li class='platform-mobileweb'\n        title='Mobile Web'>1.8</li></ul></div></div></div><div id='property-hidden' class='member  not-inherited'><a href='#' class='side expandable'><span>&nbsp;</span></a><div class='title'><div class='meta'><span class='defined-in' rel='Titanium.Filesystem.File'>Titanium.Filesystem.File</span></div><a href='#!/api/Titanium.Filesystem.File-property-hidden' class='name not-expandable'>hidden</a><span> : Boolean</span></div><div class='description'><div class='short'><p>Set to <code>true</code> if the file is hidden.</p>\n\n</div><div class='long'><p>Set to <code>true</code> if the file is hidden.</p>\n\n<p><p>On iOS, Mobile Web, this property exists but is always <code>false</code>.</p>\n\n</p></div></div></div><div id='property-lifecycleContainer' class='member  inherited'><a href='#' class='side expandable'><span>&nbsp;</span></a><div class='title'><div class='meta'><a href='#!/api/Titanium.Proxy' rel='Titanium.Proxy' class='defined-in docClass'>Titanium.Proxy</a></div><a href='#!/api/Titanium.Proxy-property-lifecycleContainer' class='name not-expandable'>lifecycleContainer</a><span> : <a href=\"#!/api/Titanium.UI.Window\" rel=\"Titanium.UI.Window\" class=\"docClass\">Titanium.UI.Window</a>/<a href=\"#!/api/Titanium.UI.TabGroup\" rel=\"Titanium.UI.TabGroup\" class=\"docClass\">Titanium.UI.TabGroup</a></span></div><div class='description'><div class='short'><p>The Window or TabGroup whose Activity lifecycle should be triggered on the proxy.</p>\n\n</div><div class='long'><p>The Window or TabGroup whose Activity lifecycle should be triggered on the proxy.</p>\n\n<p><p>If this property is set to a Window or TabGroup, then the corresponding Activity lifecycle event callbacks\nwill also be called on the proxy. Proxies that require the activity lifecycle will need this property set\nto the appropriate containing Window or TabGroup.</p>\n\n</p><ul class='platforms'><li class='platform-android'\n        title='Android'>3.6.0</li><li class='platform-windowsphone'\n        title='Window Phone'>4.1.0</li></ul></div></div></div><div id='property-name' class='member  not-inherited'><a href='#' class='side expandable'><span>&nbsp;</span></a><div class='title'><div class='meta'><span class='defined-in' rel='Titanium.Filesystem.File'>Titanium.Filesystem.File</span></div><a href='#!/api/Titanium.Filesystem.File-property-name' class='name not-expandable'>name</a><span> : String</span><strong class='readonly signature' >readonly</strong></div><div class='description'><div class='short'><p>Name of the file.</p>\n\n</div><div class='long'><p>Name of the file.</p>\n\n</div></div></div><div id='property-nativePath' class='member  not-inherited'><a href='#' class='side expandable'><span>&nbsp;</span></a><div class='title'><div class='meta'><span class='defined-in' rel='Titanium.Filesystem.File'>Titanium.Filesystem.File</span></div><a href='#!/api/Titanium.Filesystem.File-property-nativePath' class='name not-expandable'>nativePath</a><span> : String</span><strong class='readonly signature' >readonly</strong></div><div class='description'><div class='short'><p>Native path associated with this file object, as a file URL.</p>\n\n</div><div class='long'><p>Native path associated with this file object, as a file URL.</p>\n\n<p><p>On iOS, use the <a href=\"#!/api/Titanium.Filesystem.File-method-resolve\" rel=\"Titanium.Filesystem.File-method-resolve\" class=\"docClass\">resolve</a> \nmethod to obtain a plain file path for use with native modules.</p>\n\n</p></div></div></div><div id='property-parent' class='member  not-inherited'><a href='#' class='side expandable'><span>&nbsp;</span></a><div class='title'><div class='meta'><span class='defined-in' rel='Titanium.Filesystem.File'>Titanium.Filesystem.File</span></div><a href='#!/api/Titanium.Filesystem.File-property-parent' class='name not-expandable'>parent</a><span> : <a href=\"#!/api/Titanium.Filesystem.File\" rel=\"Titanium.Filesystem.File\" class=\"docClass\">Titanium.Filesystem.File</a></span><strong class='readonly signature' >readonly</strong></div><div class='description'><div class='short'><p>A <code>File</code> object representing the parent directory of the file identified by this object.</p>\n\n</div><div class='long'><p>A <code>File</code> object representing the parent directory of the file identified by this object.</p>\n\n<ul class='platforms'><li class='platform-android'\n        title='Android'>0.8</li><li class='platform-mobileweb'\n        title='Mobile Web'>1.8</li><li class='platform-windowsphone'\n        title='Window Phone'>4.1.0</li></ul></div></div></div><div id='property-readonly' class='member  not-inherited'><a href='#' class='side expandable'><span>&nbsp;</span></a><div class='title'><div class='meta'><span class='defined-in' rel='Titanium.Filesystem.File'>Titanium.Filesystem.File</span></div><a href='#!/api/Titanium.Filesystem.File-property-readonly' class='name not-expandable'>readonly</a><span> : Boolean</span><strong class='readonly signature' >readonly</strong></div><div class='description'><div class='short'><p><code>true</code> if the file identified by this object is read-only.</p>\n\n</div><div class='long'><p><code>true</code> if the file identified by this object is read-only.</p>\n\n<p><p>On Mobile Web, this property exists but is always <code>true</code> for files in the resources directory\nand <code>false</code> for application data and temporary files.</p>\n\n</p><ul class='platforms'><li class='platform-android'\n        title='Android'>0.8</li><li class='platform-mobileweb'\n        title='Mobile Web'>1.8</li><li class='platform-windowsphone'\n        title='Window Phone'>4.1.0</li></ul></div></div></div><div id='property-remoteBackup' class='member  not-inherited'><a href='#' class='side expandable'><span>&nbsp;</span></a><div class='title'><div class='meta'><span class='defined-in' rel='Titanium.Filesystem.File'>Titanium.Filesystem.File</span></div><a href='#!/api/Titanium.Filesystem.File-property-remoteBackup' class='name expandable'>remoteBackup</a><span> : Boolean</span></div><div class='description'><div class='short'>Value indicating whether or not to back up to a cloud service. ...</div><div class='long'><p>Value indicating whether or not to back up to a cloud service.</p>\n\n<p><p>Some apps may be rejected by Apple for backing up specific files; if this\nis the case, ensure that this value is set to <code>false</code> for them. This\nvalue should only need to be set once by your app, but setting it\nmultiple times will not cause problems. For files distributed with your\napp, this will need to be set on boot. This flag will only affect iOS\nversions 5.0.1 and later, but is safe to set on earlier versions.</p>\n\n\n\n\n<p>Note that setting this property to <code>false</code> will also prevent the\nfile identified by this object from being backed up to iTunes.</p>\n\n</p><p>Default: true</p><ul class='platforms'><li class='platform-iphone'\n        title='iPhone'>1.8.0</li><li class='platform-ipad'\n        title='iPad'>1.8.0</li></ul></div></div></div><div id='property-size' class='member  not-inherited'><a href='#' class='side expandable'><span>&nbsp;</span></a><div class='title'><div class='meta'><span class='defined-in' rel='Titanium.Filesystem.File'>Titanium.Filesystem.File</span></div><a href='#!/api/Titanium.Filesystem.File-property-size' class='name not-expandable'>size</a><span> : Number</span><strong class='readonly signature' >readonly</strong></div><div class='description'><div class='short'><p>Size, in bytes, of the file identified by this object.</p>\n\n</div><div class='long'><p>Size, in bytes, of the file identified by this object.</p>\n\n</div></div></div><div id='property-symbolicLink' class='member  not-inherited'><a href='#' class='side expandable'><span>&nbsp;</span></a><div class='title'><div class='meta'><span class='defined-in' rel='Titanium.Filesystem.File'>Titanium.Filesystem.File</span></div><a href='#!/api/Titanium.Filesystem.File-property-symbolicLink' class='name not-expandable'>symbolicLink</a><span> : Boolean</span><strong class='readonly signature' >readonly</strong></div><div class='description'><div class='short'><p><code>true</code> if the file identified by this object is a symbolic link.</p>\n\n</div><div class='long'><p><code>true</code> if the file identified by this object is a symbolic link.</p>\n\n<p><p>On Mobile Web, this property exists but is always <code>false</code>.</p>\n\n</p><ul class='platforms'><li class='platform-android'\n        title='Android'>0.8</li><li class='platform-iphone'\n        title='iPhone'>0.8</li><li class='platform-ipad'\n        title='iPad'>0.8</li><li class='platform-mobileweb'\n        title='Mobile Web'>1.8</li></ul></div></div></div><div id='property-writable' class='member  not-inherited'><a href='#' class='side expandable'><span>&nbsp;</span></a><div class='title'><div class='meta'><span class='defined-in' rel='Titanium.Filesystem.File'>Titanium.Filesystem.File</span></div><a href='#!/api/Titanium.Filesystem.File-property-writable' class='name not-expandable'>writable</a><span> : Boolean</span><strong class='readonly signature' >readonly</strong></div><div class='description'><div class='short'><p><code>true</code> if the file identified by this object is writable.</p>\n\n</div><div class='long'><p><code>true</code> if the file identified by this object is writable.</p>\n\n</div></div></div><div id='property-writeable' class='member  not-inherited'><a href='#' class='side expandable'><span>&nbsp;</span></a><div class='title'><div class='meta'><span class='defined-in' rel='Titanium.Filesystem.File'>Titanium.Filesystem.File</span></div><a href='#!/api/Titanium.Filesystem.File-property-writeable' class='name not-expandable'>writeable</a><span> : Boolean</span><strong class='readonly signature' >readonly</strong><strong class='removed signature' >removed</strong></div><div class='description'><div class='short'><p><code>true</code> if the file identified by this object is writable.</p>\n\n</div><div class='long'><p><code>true</code> if the file identified by this object is writable.</p>\n\n        <div class='signature-box removed'>\n        <p>This property has been <strong>removed</strong> since 6.0.0</p>\n        <p>Use <a href=\"Titanium.Filesystem.File.writable\">writable</a> instead.</p>\n\n        </div>\n<ul class='platforms'><li class='platform-iphone'\n        title='iPhone'>0.8</li><li class='platform-ipad'\n        title='iPad'>0.8</li></ul></div></div></div></div></div><div class='members-section'><div class='definedBy'>Defined By</div><h3 class='members-title icon-method'>Methods</h3><div class='subsection'><div id='method-addEventListener' class='member first-child inherited'><a href='#' class='side expandable'><span>&nbsp;</span></a><div class='title'><div class='meta'><a href='#!/api/Titanium.Proxy' rel='Titanium.Proxy' class='defined-in docClass'>Titanium.Proxy</a></div><a href='#!/api/Titanium.Proxy-method-addEventListener' class='name expandable'>addEventListener</a>( <span class='pre'>name, callback</span> )</div><div class='description'><div class='short'>Adds the specified callback as an event listener for the named event. ...</div><div class='long'><p>Adds the specified callback as an event listener for the named event.</p>\n\n<h3 class=\"pa\">Parameters</h3><ul><li><span class='pre'>name</span> : String<div class='sub-desc'><p>Name of the event.</p>\n\n</div></li><li><span class='pre'>callback</span> : Callback&lt;Object&gt;<div class='sub-desc'><p>Callback function to invoke when the event is fired.</p>\n\n</div></li></ul><h3 class='pa'>Returns</h3><ul><li><span class='pre'>void</span></li></ul></div></div></div><div id='method-append' class='member  not-inherited'><a href='#' class='side expandable'><span>&nbsp;</span></a><div class='title'><div class='meta'><span class='defined-in' rel='Titanium.Filesystem.File'>Titanium.Filesystem.File</span></div><a href='#!/api/Titanium.Filesystem.File-method-append' class='name expandable'>append</a>( <span class='pre'>data</span> ) : Boolean</div><div class='description'><div class='short'>Appends data to the file identified by this file object. ...</div><div class='long'><p>Appends data to the file identified by this file object.</p>\n\n<p><p>Data to append can be specified as a String, <code>Blob</code>, or <code>File</code>.</p>\n\n\n\n\n<p>If the <code>data</code> argument is a <code>File</code> object, the file's contents\nare appended to this file.</p>\n\n\n\n\n<p>Returns <code>true</code> if the operation succeeds.</p>\n\n</p><ul class='platforms'><li class='platform-iphone'\n        title='iPhone'>0.8</li><li class='platform-ipad'\n        title='iPad'>0.8</li><li class='platform-mobileweb'\n        title='Mobile Web'>1.8</li><li class='platform-windowsphone'\n        title='Window Phone'>4.1.0</li></ul><h3 class=\"pa\">Parameters</h3><ul><li><span class='pre'>data</span> : String/<a href=\"#!/api/Titanium.Blob\" rel=\"Titanium.Blob\" class=\"docClass\">Titanium.Blob</a>/<a href=\"#!/api/Titanium.Filesystem.File\" rel=\"Titanium.Filesystem.File\" class=\"docClass\">Titanium.Filesystem.File</a><div class='sub-desc'><p>Data to append.</p>\n\n</div></li></ul><h3 class='pa'>Returns</h3><ul><li><span class='pre'>Boolean</span><div class='sub-desc'>\n</div></li></ul></div></div></div><div id='method-applyProperties' class='member  inherited'><a href='#' class='side expandable'><span>&nbsp;</span></a><div class='title'><div class='meta'><a href='#!/api/Titanium.Proxy' rel='Titanium.Proxy' class='defined-in docClass'>Titanium.Proxy</a></div><a href='#!/api/Titanium.Proxy-method-applyProperties' class='name expandable'>applyProperties</a>( <span class='pre'>props</span> )</div><div class='description'><div class='short'>Applies the properties to the proxy. ...</div><div class='long'><p>Applies the properties to the proxy.</p>\n\n<p><p>Properties are supplied as a dictionary. Each key-value pair in the object is applied to the proxy such that\nmyproxy[key] = value.</p>\n\n</p><ul class='platforms'><li class='platform-android'\n        title='Android'>3.0.0</li><li class='platform-iphone'\n        title='iPhone'>3.0.0</li><li class='platform-ipad'\n        title='iPad'>3.0.0</li><li class='platform-mobileweb'\n        title='Mobile Web'>3.0.0</li><li class='platform-windowsphone'\n        title='Window Phone'>4.1.0</li></ul><h3 class=\"pa\">Parameters</h3><ul><li><span class='pre'>props</span> : <a href=\"#!/api/Dictionary\" rel=\"Dictionary\" class=\"docClass\">Dictionary</a><div class='sub-desc'><p>A dictionary of properties to apply.</p>\n\n</div></li></ul><h3 class='pa'>Returns</h3><ul><li><span class='pre'>void</span></li></ul></div></div></div><div id='method-copy' class='member  not-inherited'><a href='#' class='side expandable'><span>&nbsp;</span></a><div class='title'><div class='meta'><span class='defined-in' rel='Titanium.Filesystem.File'>Titanium.Filesystem.File</span></div><a href='#!/api/Titanium.Filesystem.File-method-copy' class='name expandable'>copy</a>( <span class='pre'>destinationPath</span> ) : Boolean</div><div class='description'><div class='short'>Copies the file identified by this file object to a new path. ...</div><div class='long'><p>Copies the file identified by this file object to a new path.</p>\n\n<p><p>Returns <code>true</code> if the copy succeeds.</p>\n\n</p><ul class='platforms'><li class='platform-android'\n        title='Android'>0.8</li><li class='platform-mobileweb'\n        title='Mobile Web'>1.8</li><li class='platform-windowsphone'\n        title='Window Phone'>4.1.0</li></ul><h3 class=\"pa\">Parameters</h3><ul><li><span class='pre'>destinationPath</span> : String<div class='sub-desc'><p>Destination path to copy to.</p>\n\n</div></li></ul><h3 class='pa'>Returns</h3><ul><li><span class='pre'>Boolean</span><div class='sub-desc'>\n</div></li></ul></div></div></div><div id='method-createDirectory' class='member  not-inherited'><a href='#' class='side expandable'><span>&nbsp;</span></a><div class='title'><div class='meta'><span class='defined-in' rel='Titanium.Filesystem.File'>Titanium.Filesystem.File</span></div><a href='#!/api/Titanium.Filesystem.File-method-createDirectory' class='name expandable'>createDirectory</a>( <span class='pre'></span> ) : Boolean</div><div class='description'><div class='short'>Creates a directory at the path identified by this file object. ...</div><div class='long'><p>Creates a directory at the path identified by this file object.</p>\n\n<p><p>Returns <code>true</code> if the directory was created successfully.</p>\n\n</p><h3 class='pa'>Returns</h3><ul><li><span class='pre'>Boolean</span><div class='sub-desc'>\n</div></li></ul></div></div></div><div id='method-createFile' class='member  not-inherited'><a href='#' class='side expandable'><span>&nbsp;</span></a><div class='title'><div class='meta'><span class='defined-in' rel='Titanium.Filesystem.File'>Titanium.Filesystem.File</span></div><a href='#!/api/Titanium.Filesystem.File-method-createFile' class='name expandable'>createFile</a>( <span class='pre'></span> ) : Boolean</div><div class='description'><div class='short'>Creates a file at the path identified by this file object. ...</div><div class='long'><p>Creates a file at the path identified by this file object.</p>\n\n<p><p>Note that if you write to a file that doesn't exist, the file is created automatically,\nso it is not necessary to call this method unless you want to explicitly create the file\n(for example, to create an empty file).</p>\n\n\n\n\n<p>Returns <code>true</code> if the file was created successfully. Returns <code>false</code> if the \nfile already exists, or if the file couldn't be created for some other reason.</p>\n\n</p><ul class='platforms'><li class='platform-iphone'\n        title='iPhone'>0.8</li><li class='platform-ipad'\n        title='iPad'>0.8</li><li class='platform-mobileweb'\n        title='Mobile Web'>1.8</li><li class='platform-windowsphone'\n        title='Window Phone'>4.1.0</li></ul><h3 class='pa'>Returns</h3><ul><li><span class='pre'>Boolean</span><div class='sub-desc'>\n</div></li></ul></div></div></div><div id='method-createTimestamp' class='member  not-inherited'><a href='#' class='side expandable'><span>&nbsp;</span></a><div class='title'><div class='meta'><span class='defined-in' rel='Titanium.Filesystem.File'>Titanium.Filesystem.File</span></div><a href='#!/api/Titanium.Filesystem.File-method-createTimestamp' class='name expandable'>createTimestamp</a>( <span class='pre'></span> ) : Number</div><div class='description'><div class='short'>Returns the creation timestamp for the file identified by this file object. ...</div><div class='long'><p>Returns the creation timestamp for the file identified by this file object.</p>\n\n<p><p>On Android, returns 0 for resource files.</p>\n\n</p><h3 class='pa'>Returns</h3><ul><li><span class='pre'>Number</span><div class='sub-desc'>\n</div></li></ul></div></div></div><div id='method-deleteDirectory' class='member  not-inherited'><a href='#' class='side expandable'><span>&nbsp;</span></a><div class='title'><div class='meta'><span class='defined-in' rel='Titanium.Filesystem.File'>Titanium.Filesystem.File</span></div><a href='#!/api/Titanium.Filesystem.File-method-deleteDirectory' class='name expandable'>deleteDirectory</a>( <span class='pre'>[recursive]</span> ) : Boolean</div><div class='description'><div class='short'>Deletes the directory identified by this file object. ...</div><div class='long'><p>Deletes the directory identified by this file object.</p>\n\n<p><p>Returns <code>true</code> if the operation was successful. Does nothing if the file\nobject does not identify a directory.</p>\n\n</p><h3 class=\"pa\">Parameters</h3><ul><li><span class='pre'>recursive</span> : Boolean (optional)<div class='sub-desc'><p>Pass <code>true</code> to recursively delete any directory contents.</p>\n\n</div></li></ul><h3 class='pa'>Returns</h3><ul><li><span class='pre'>Boolean</span><div class='sub-desc'>\n</div></li></ul></div></div></div><div id='method-deleteFile' class='member  not-inherited'><a href='#' class='side expandable'><span>&nbsp;</span></a><div class='title'><div class='meta'><span class='defined-in' rel='Titanium.Filesystem.File'>Titanium.Filesystem.File</span></div><a href='#!/api/Titanium.Filesystem.File-method-deleteFile' class='name expandable'>deleteFile</a>( <span class='pre'></span> ) : Boolean</div><div class='description'><div class='short'>Deletes the file identified by this file object. ...</div><div class='long'><p>Deletes the file identified by this file object.</p>\n\n<p><p>Returns <code>true</code> if the operation was successful.</p>\n\n</p><h3 class='pa'>Returns</h3><ul><li><span class='pre'>Boolean</span><div class='sub-desc'>\n</div></li></ul></div></div></div><div id='method-exists' class='member  not-inherited'><a href='#' class='side expandable'><span>&nbsp;</span></a><div class='title'><div class='meta'><span class='defined-in' rel='Titanium.Filesystem.File'>Titanium.Filesystem.File</span></div><a href='#!/api/Titanium.Filesystem.File-method-exists' class='name expandable'>exists</a>( <span class='pre'></span> ) : Boolean</div><div class='description'><div class='short'>Returns true if the file or directory identified by this file object exists on the device. ...</div><div class='long'><p>Returns <code>true</code> if the file or directory identified by this file object exists on the device.</p>\n\n<h3 class='pa'>Returns</h3><ul><li><span class='pre'>Boolean</span><div class='sub-desc'>\n</div></li></ul></div></div></div><div id='method-extension' class='member  not-inherited'><a href='#' class='side expandable'><span>&nbsp;</span></a><div class='title'><div class='meta'><span class='defined-in' rel='Titanium.Filesystem.File'>Titanium.Filesystem.File</span></div><a href='#!/api/Titanium.Filesystem.File-method-extension' class='name expandable'>extension</a>( <span class='pre'></span> ) : String</div><div class='description'><div class='short'>Returns the extension for the file identified by this file object. ...</div><div class='long'><p>Returns the extension for the file identified by this file object.</p>\n\n<h3 class='pa'>Returns</h3><ul><li><span class='pre'>String</span><div class='sub-desc'>\n</div></li></ul></div></div></div><div id='method-fireEvent' class='member  inherited'><a href='#' class='side expandable'><span>&nbsp;</span></a><div class='title'><div class='meta'><a href='#!/api/Titanium.Proxy' rel='Titanium.Proxy' class='defined-in docClass'>Titanium.Proxy</a></div><a href='#!/api/Titanium.Proxy-method-fireEvent' class='name expandable'>fireEvent</a>( <span class='pre'>name, event</span> )</div><div class='description'><div class='short'>Fires a synthesized event to any registered listeners. ...</div><div class='long'><p>Fires a synthesized event to any registered listeners.</p>\n\n<h3 class=\"pa\">Parameters</h3><ul><li><span class='pre'>name</span> : String<div class='sub-desc'><p>Name of the event.</p>\n\n</div></li><li><span class='pre'>event</span> : <a href=\"#!/api/Dictionary\" rel=\"Dictionary\" class=\"docClass\">Dictionary</a><div class='sub-desc'><p>A dictionary of keys and values to add to the <a href=\"#!/api/Titanium.Event\" rel=\"Titanium.Event\" class=\"docClass\">Titanium.Event</a> object sent to the listeners.</p>\n\n</div></li></ul><h3 class='pa'>Returns</h3><ul><li><span class='pre'>void</span></li></ul></div></div></div><div id='method-getApiName' class='member  inherited'><a href='#' class='side expandable'><span>&nbsp;</span></a><div class='title'><div class='meta'><a href='#!/api/Titanium.Proxy' rel='Titanium.Proxy' class='defined-in docClass'>Titanium.Proxy</a></div><a href='#!/api/Titanium.Proxy-method-getApiName' class='name expandable'>getApiName</a>( <span class='pre'></span> ) : String</div><div class='description'><div class='short'>Gets the value of the apiName property. ...</div><div class='long'><p>Gets the value of the <a href=\"#!/api/Titanium.Proxy-property-apiName\" rel=\"Titanium.Proxy-property-apiName\" class=\"docClass\">apiName</a> property.</p>\n\n<ul class='platforms'><li class='platform-android'\n        title='Android'>3.2.0</li><li class='platform-iphone'\n        title='iPhone'>3.2.0</li><li class='platform-ipad'\n        title='iPad'>3.2.0</li><li class='platform-mobileweb'\n        title='Mobile Web'>3.2.0</li><li class='platform-windowsphone'\n        title='Window Phone'>4.1.0</li></ul><h3 class='pa'>Returns</h3><ul><li><span class='pre'>String</span><div class='sub-desc'>\n</div></li></ul></div></div></div><div id='method-getBubbleParent' class='member  inherited'><a href='#' class='side expandable'><span>&nbsp;</span></a><div class='title'><div class='meta'><a href='#!/api/Titanium.Proxy' rel='Titanium.Proxy' class='defined-in docClass'>Titanium.Proxy</a></div><a href='#!/api/Titanium.Proxy-method-getBubbleParent' class='name expandable'>getBubbleParent</a>( <span class='pre'></span> ) : Boolean</div><div class='description'><div class='short'>Gets the value of the bubbleParent property. ...</div><div class='long'><p>Gets the value of the <a href=\"#!/api/Titanium.Proxy-property-bubbleParent\" rel=\"Titanium.Proxy-property-bubbleParent\" class=\"docClass\">bubbleParent</a> property.</p>\n\n<ul class='platforms'><li class='platform-android'\n        title='Android'>3.0.0</li><li class='platform-iphone'\n        title='iPhone'>3.0.0</li><li class='platform-ipad'\n        title='iPad'>3.0.0</li><li class='platform-windowsphone'\n        title='Window Phone'>4.1.0</li></ul><h3 class='pa'>Returns</h3><ul><li><span class='pre'>Boolean</span><div class='sub-desc'>\n</div></li></ul></div></div></div><div id='method-getDirectoryListing' class='member  not-inherited'><a href='#' class='side expandable'><span>&nbsp;</span></a><div class='title'><div class='meta'><span class='defined-in' rel='Titanium.Filesystem.File'>Titanium.Filesystem.File</span></div><a href='#!/api/Titanium.Filesystem.File-method-getDirectoryListing' class='name expandable'>getDirectoryListing</a>( <span class='pre'></span> ) : String[]</div><div class='description'><div class='short'>Returns a listing of the directory identified by this file object, or null\nif this object doesn't identify a directory. ...</div><div class='long'><p>Returns a listing of the directory identified by this file object, or <code>null</code>\nif this object doesn't identify a directory.</p>\n\n<h3 class='pa'>Returns</h3><ul><li><span class='pre'>String[]</span><div class='sub-desc'>\n</div></li></ul></div></div></div><div id='method-getExecutable' class='member  not-inherited'><a href='#' class='side expandable'><span>&nbsp;</span></a><div class='title'><div class='meta'><span class='defined-in' rel='Titanium.Filesystem.File'>Titanium.Filesystem.File</span></div><a href='#!/api/Titanium.Filesystem.File-method-getExecutable' class='name expandable'>getExecutable</a>( <span class='pre'></span> ) : Boolean</div><div class='description'><div class='short'>Gets the value of the executable property. ...</div><div class='long'><p>Gets the value of the <a href=\"#!/api/Titanium.Filesystem.File-property-executable\" rel=\"Titanium.Filesystem.File-property-executable\" class=\"docClass\">executable</a> property.</p>\n\n<ul class='platforms'><li class='platform-android'\n        title='Android'>0.8</li><li class='platform-iphone'\n        title='iPhone'>0.8</li><li class='platform-ipad'\n        title='iPad'>0.8</li><li class='platform-mobileweb'\n        title='Mobile Web'>1.8</li></ul><h3 class='pa'>Returns</h3><ul><li><span class='pre'>Boolean</span><div class='sub-desc'>\n</div></li></ul></div></div></div><div id='method-getHidden' class='member  not-inherited'><a href='#' class='side expandable'><span>&nbsp;</span></a><div class='title'><div class='meta'><span class='defined-in' rel='Titanium.Filesystem.File'>Titanium.Filesystem.File</span></div><a href='#!/api/Titanium.Filesystem.File-method-getHidden' class='name expandable'>getHidden</a>( <span class='pre'></span> ) : Boolean</div><div class='description'><div class='short'>Gets the value of the hidden property. ...</div><div class='long'><p>Gets the value of the <a href=\"#!/api/Titanium.Filesystem.File-property-hidden\" rel=\"Titanium.Filesystem.File-property-hidden\" class=\"docClass\">hidden</a> property.</p>\n\n<h3 class='pa'>Returns</h3><ul><li><span class='pre'>Boolean</span><div class='sub-desc'>\n</div></li></ul></div></div></div><div id='method-getLifecycleContainer' class='member  inherited'><a href='#' class='side expandable'><span>&nbsp;</span></a><div class='title'><div class='meta'><a href='#!/api/Titanium.Proxy' rel='Titanium.Proxy' class='defined-in docClass'>Titanium.Proxy</a></div><a href='#!/api/Titanium.Proxy-method-getLifecycleContainer' class='name expandable'>getLifecycleContainer</a>( <span class='pre'></span> ) : <a href=\"#!/api/Titanium.UI.Window\" rel=\"Titanium.UI.Window\" class=\"docClass\">Titanium.UI.Window</a>/<a href=\"#!/api/Titanium.UI.TabGroup\" rel=\"Titanium.UI.TabGroup\" class=\"docClass\">Titanium.UI.TabGroup</a></div><div class='description'><div class='short'>Gets the value of the lifecycleContainer property. ...</div><div class='long'><p>Gets the value of the <a href=\"#!/api/Titanium.Proxy-property-lifecycleContainer\" rel=\"Titanium.Proxy-property-lifecycleContainer\" class=\"docClass\">lifecycleContainer</a> property.</p>\n\n<ul class='platforms'><li class='platform-android'\n        title='Android'>3.6.0</li><li class='platform-windowsphone'\n        title='Window Phone'>4.1.0</li></ul><h3 class='pa'>Returns</h3><ul><li><span class='pre'><a href=\"#!/api/Titanium.UI.Window\" rel=\"Titanium.UI.Window\" class=\"docClass\">Titanium.UI.Window</a>/<a href=\"#!/api/Titanium.UI.TabGroup\" rel=\"Titanium.UI.TabGroup\" class=\"docClass\">Titanium.UI.TabGroup</a></span><div class='sub-desc'>\n</div></li></ul></div></div></div><div id='method-getName' class='member  not-inherited'><a href='#' class='side expandable'><span>&nbsp;</span></a><div class='title'><div class='meta'><span class='defined-in' rel='Titanium.Filesystem.File'>Titanium.Filesystem.File</span></div><a href='#!/api/Titanium.Filesystem.File-method-getName' class='name expandable'>getName</a>( <span class='pre'></span> ) : String</div><div class='description'><div class='short'>Gets the value of the name property. ...</div><div class='long'><p>Gets the value of the <a href=\"#!/api/Titanium.Filesystem.File-property-name\" rel=\"Titanium.Filesystem.File-property-name\" class=\"docClass\">name</a> property.</p>\n\n<h3 class='pa'>Returns</h3><ul><li><span class='pre'>String</span><div class='sub-desc'>\n</div></li></ul></div></div></div><div id='method-getNativePath' class='member  not-inherited'><a href='#' class='side expandable'><span>&nbsp;</span></a><div class='title'><div class='meta'><span class='defined-in' rel='Titanium.Filesystem.File'>Titanium.Filesystem.File</span></div><a href='#!/api/Titanium.Filesystem.File-method-getNativePath' class='name expandable'>getNativePath</a>( <span class='pre'></span> ) : String</div><div class='description'><div class='short'>Gets the value of the nativePath property. ...</div><div class='long'><p>Gets the value of the <a href=\"#!/api/Titanium.Filesystem.File-property-nativePath\" rel=\"Titanium.Filesystem.File-property-nativePath\" class=\"docClass\">nativePath</a> property.</p>\n\n<h3 class='pa'>Returns</h3><ul><li><span class='pre'>String</span><div class='sub-desc'>\n</div></li></ul></div></div></div><div id='method-getParent' class='member  not-inherited'><a href='#' class='side expandable'><span>&nbsp;</span></a><div class='title'><div class='meta'><span class='defined-in' rel='Titanium.Filesystem.File'>Titanium.Filesystem.File</span></div><a href='#!/api/Titanium.Filesystem.File-method-getParent' class='name expandable'>getParent</a>( <span class='pre'></span> ) : <a href=\"#!/api/Titanium.Filesystem.File\" rel=\"Titanium.Filesystem.File\" class=\"docClass\">Titanium.Filesystem.File</a></div><div class='description'><div class='short'>Gets the value of the parent property. ...</div><div class='long'><p>Gets the value of the <a href=\"#!/api/Titanium.Filesystem.File-property-parent\" rel=\"Titanium.Filesystem.File-property-parent\" class=\"docClass\">parent</a> property.</p>\n\n<ul class='platforms'><li class='platform-android'\n        title='Android'>0.8</li><li class='platform-mobileweb'\n        title='Mobile Web'>1.8</li><li class='platform-windowsphone'\n        title='Window Phone'>4.1.0</li></ul><h3 class='pa'>Returns</h3><ul><li><span class='pre'><a href=\"#!/api/Titanium.Filesystem.File\" rel=\"Titanium.Filesystem.File\" class=\"docClass\">Titanium.Filesystem.File</a></span><div class='sub-desc'>\n</div></li></ul></div></div></div><div id='method-getProtectionKey' class='member  not-inherited'><a href='#' class='side expandable'><span>&nbsp;</span></a><div class='title'><div class='meta'><span class='defined-in' rel='Titanium.Filesystem.File'>Titanium.Filesystem.File</span></div><a href='#!/api/Titanium.Filesystem.File-method-getProtectionKey' class='name expandable'>getProtectionKey</a>( <span class='pre'></span> ) : String</div><div class='description'><div class='short'>Returns the protection key value of this file object. ...</div><div class='long'><p>Returns the protection key value of this file object.\nReturns <code>null</code> if there's an error.</p>\n\n<ul class='platforms'><li class='platform-iphone'\n        title='iPhone'>4.1.0</li><li class='platform-ipad'\n        title='iPad'>4.1.0</li></ul><h3 class='pa'>Returns</h3><ul><li><span class='pre'>String</span><div class='sub-desc'><p>This API can be assigned the following constants:<ul>\n <li> <a href=\"#!/api/Titanium.Filesystem-property-IOS_FILE_PROTECTION_NONE\" rel=\"Titanium.Filesystem-property-IOS_FILE_PROTECTION_NONE\" class=\"docClass\">Titanium.Filesystem.IOS_FILE_PROTECTION_NONE</a>\n <li> <a href=\"#!/api/Titanium.Filesystem-property-IOS_FILE_PROTECTION_COMPLETE\" rel=\"Titanium.Filesystem-property-IOS_FILE_PROTECTION_COMPLETE\" class=\"docClass\">Titanium.Filesystem.IOS_FILE_PROTECTION_COMPLETE</a>\n <li> <a href=\"#!/api/Titanium.Filesystem-property-IOS_FILE_PROTECTION_COMPLETE_UNLESS_OPEN\" rel=\"Titanium.Filesystem-property-IOS_FILE_PROTECTION_COMPLETE_UNLESS_OPEN\" class=\"docClass\">Titanium.Filesystem.IOS_FILE_PROTECTION_COMPLETE_UNLESS_OPEN</a>\n <li> <a href=\"#!/api/Titanium.Filesystem-property-IOS_FILE_PROTECTION_COMPLETE_UNTIL_FIRST_USER_AUTHENTICATION\" rel=\"Titanium.Filesystem-property-IOS_FILE_PROTECTION_COMPLETE_UNTIL_FIRST_USER_AUTHENTICATION\" class=\"docClass\">Titanium.Filesystem.IOS_FILE_PROTECTION_COMPLETE_UNTIL_FIRST_USER_AUTHENTICATION</a>\n</li></li></li></li></ul></p>\n\n</div></li></ul></div></div></div><div id='method-getReadonly' class='member  not-inherited'><a href='#' class='side expandable'><span>&nbsp;</span></a><div class='title'><div class='meta'><span class='defined-in' rel='Titanium.Filesystem.File'>Titanium.Filesystem.File</span></div><a href='#!/api/Titanium.Filesystem.File-method-getReadonly' class='name expandable'>getReadonly</a>( <span class='pre'></span> ) : Boolean</div><div class='description'><div class='short'>Gets the value of the readonly property. ...</div><div class='long'><p>Gets the value of the <a href=\"#!/api/Titanium.Filesystem.File-property-readonly\" rel=\"Titanium.Filesystem.File-property-readonly\" class=\"docClass\">readonly</a> property.</p>\n\n<ul class='platforms'><li class='platform-android'\n        title='Android'>0.8</li><li class='platform-mobileweb'\n        title='Mobile Web'>1.8</li><li class='platform-windowsphone'\n        title='Window Phone'>4.1.0</li></ul><h3 class='pa'>Returns</h3><ul><li><span class='pre'>Boolean</span><div class='sub-desc'>\n</div></li></ul></div></div></div><div id='method-getRemoteBackup' class='member  not-inherited'><a href='#' class='side expandable'><span>&nbsp;</span></a><div class='title'><div class='meta'><span class='defined-in' rel='Titanium.Filesystem.File'>Titanium.Filesystem.File</span></div><a href='#!/api/Titanium.Filesystem.File-method-getRemoteBackup' class='name expandable'>getRemoteBackup</a>( <span class='pre'></span> ) : Boolean</div><div class='description'><div class='short'>Gets the value of the remoteBackup property. ...</div><div class='long'><p>Gets the value of the <a href=\"#!/api/Titanium.Filesystem.File-property-remoteBackup\" rel=\"Titanium.Filesystem.File-property-remoteBackup\" class=\"docClass\">remoteBackup</a> property.</p>\n\n<ul class='platforms'><li class='platform-iphone'\n        title='iPhone'>1.8.0</li><li class='platform-ipad'\n        title='iPad'>1.8.0</li></ul><h3 class='pa'>Returns</h3><ul><li><span class='pre'>Boolean</span><div class='sub-desc'>\n</div></li></ul></div></div></div><div id='method-getSize' class='member  not-inherited'><a href='#' class='side expandable'><span>&nbsp;</span></a><div class='title'><div class='meta'><span class='defined-in' rel='Titanium.Filesystem.File'>Titanium.Filesystem.File</span></div><a href='#!/api/Titanium.Filesystem.File-method-getSize' class='name expandable'>getSize</a>( <span class='pre'></span> ) : Number</div><div class='description'><div class='short'>Gets the value of the size property. ...</div><div class='long'><p>Gets the value of the <a href=\"#!/api/Titanium.Filesystem.File-property-size\" rel=\"Titanium.Filesystem.File-property-size\" class=\"docClass\">size</a> property.</p>\n\n<h3 class='pa'>Returns</h3><ul><li><span class='pre'>Number</span><div class='sub-desc'>\n</div></li></ul></div></div></div><div id='method-getSymbolicLink' class='member  not-inherited'><a href='#' class='side expandable'><span>&nbsp;</span></a><div class='title'><div class='meta'><span class='defined-in' rel='Titanium.Filesystem.File'>Titanium.Filesystem.File</span></div><a href='#!/api/Titanium.Filesystem.File-method-getSymbolicLink' class='name expandable'>getSymbolicLink</a>( <span class='pre'></span> ) : Boolean</div><div class='description'><div class='short'>Gets the value of the symbolicLink property. ...</div><div class='long'><p>Gets the value of the <a href=\"#!/api/Titanium.Filesystem.File-property-symbolicLink\" rel=\"Titanium.Filesystem.File-property-symbolicLink\" class=\"docClass\">symbolicLink</a> property.</p>\n\n<ul class='platforms'><li class='platform-android'\n        title='Android'>0.8</li><li class='platform-iphone'\n        title='iPhone'>0.8</li><li class='platform-ipad'\n        title='iPad'>0.8</li><li class='platform-mobileweb'\n        title='Mobile Web'>1.8</li></ul><h3 class='pa'>Returns</h3><ul><li><span class='pre'>Boolean</span><div class='sub-desc'>\n</div></li></ul></div></div></div><div id='method-getWritable' class='member  not-inherited'><a href='#' class='side expandable'><span>&nbsp;</span></a><div class='title'><div class='meta'><span class='defined-in' rel='Titanium.Filesystem.File'>Titanium.Filesystem.File</span></div><a href='#!/api/Titanium.Filesystem.File-method-getWritable' class='name expandable'>getWritable</a>( <span class='pre'></span> ) : Boolean</div><div class='description'><div class='short'>Gets the value of the writable property. ...</div><div class='long'><p>Gets the value of the <a href=\"#!/api/Titanium.Filesystem.File-property-writable\" rel=\"Titanium.Filesystem.File-property-writable\" class=\"docClass\">writable</a> property.</p>\n\n<h3 class='pa'>Returns</h3><ul><li><span class='pre'>Boolean</span><div class='sub-desc'>\n</div></li></ul></div></div></div><div id='method-getWriteable' class='member  not-inherited'><a href='#' class='side expandable'><span>&nbsp;</span></a><div class='title'><div class='meta'><span class='defined-in' rel='Titanium.Filesystem.File'>Titanium.Filesystem.File</span></div><a href='#!/api/Titanium.Filesystem.File-method-getWriteable' class='name expandable'>getWriteable</a>( <span class='pre'></span> ) : Boolean<strong class='removed signature' >removed</strong></div><div class='description'><div class='short'>Gets the value of the writeable property. ...</div><div class='long'><p>Gets the value of the <a href=\"#!/api/Titanium.Filesystem.File-property-writeable\" rel=\"Titanium.Filesystem.File-property-writeable\" class=\"docClass\">writeable</a> property.</p>\n\n        <div class='signature-box removed'>\n        <p>This method has been <strong>removed</strong> since 6.0.0</p>\n        <p>Use <a href=\"Titanium.Filesystem.File.writable\">writable</a> instead.</p>\n\n        </div>\n<ul class='platforms'><li class='platform-iphone'\n        title='iPhone'>0.8</li><li class='platform-ipad'\n        title='iPad'>0.8</li></ul><h3 class='pa'>Returns</h3><ul><li><span class='pre'>Boolean</span><div class='sub-desc'>\n</div></li></ul></div></div></div><div id='method-isDirectory' class='member  not-inherited'><a href='#' class='side expandable'><span>&nbsp;</span></a><div class='title'><div class='meta'><span class='defined-in' rel='Titanium.Filesystem.File'>Titanium.Filesystem.File</span></div><a href='#!/api/Titanium.Filesystem.File-method-isDirectory' class='name expandable'>isDirectory</a>( <span class='pre'></span> ) : Boolean</div><div class='description'><div class='short'>Returns true if this file object represents a directory. ...</div><div class='long'><p>Returns <code>true</code> if this file object represents a directory.</p>\n\n<ul class='platforms'><li class='platform-android'\n        title='Android'>0.8</li><li class='platform-iphone'\n        title='iPhone'>3.1.0</li><li class='platform-ipad'\n        title='iPad'>3.1.0</li><li class='platform-mobileweb'\n        title='Mobile Web'>1.8</li><li class='platform-windowsphone'\n        title='Window Phone'>4.1.0</li></ul><h3 class='pa'>Returns</h3><ul><li><span class='pre'>Boolean</span><div class='sub-desc'>\n</div></li></ul></div></div></div><div id='method-isFile' class='member  not-inherited'><a href='#' class='side expandable'><span>&nbsp;</span></a><div class='title'><div class='meta'><span class='defined-in' rel='Titanium.Filesystem.File'>Titanium.Filesystem.File</span></div><a href='#!/api/Titanium.Filesystem.File-method-isFile' class='name expandable'>isFile</a>( <span class='pre'></span> ) : Boolean</div><div class='description'><div class='short'>Returns true if this file object represents an ordinary file. ...</div><div class='long'><p>Returns <code>true</code> if this file object represents an ordinary file.</p>\n\n<ul class='platforms'><li class='platform-android'\n        title='Android'>0.8</li><li class='platform-iphone'\n        title='iPhone'>3.1.0</li><li class='platform-ipad'\n        title='iPad'>3.1.0</li><li class='platform-mobileweb'\n        title='Mobile Web'>1.8</li><li class='platform-windowsphone'\n        title='Window Phone'>4.1.0</li></ul><h3 class='pa'>Returns</h3><ul><li><span class='pre'>Boolean</span><div class='sub-desc'>\n</div></li></ul></div></div></div><div id='method-modificationTimestamp' class='member  not-inherited'><a href='#' class='side expandable'><span>&nbsp;</span></a><div class='title'><div class='meta'><span class='defined-in' rel='Titanium.Filesystem.File'>Titanium.Filesystem.File</span></div><a href='#!/api/Titanium.Filesystem.File-method-modificationTimestamp' class='name expandable'>modificationTimestamp</a>( <span class='pre'></span> ) : Number</div><div class='description'><div class='short'>Returns the last modification time for this file. ...</div><div class='long'><p>Returns the last modification time for this file.</p>\n\n<p><p>On Android, returns 0 for resource files.</p>\n\n</p><h3 class='pa'>Returns</h3><ul><li><span class='pre'>Number</span><div class='sub-desc'>\n</div></li></ul></div></div></div><div id='method-move' class='member  not-inherited'><a href='#' class='side expandable'><span>&nbsp;</span></a><div class='title'><div class='meta'><span class='defined-in' rel='Titanium.Filesystem.File'>Titanium.Filesystem.File</span></div><a href='#!/api/Titanium.Filesystem.File-method-move' class='name expandable'>move</a>( <span class='pre'>newpath</span> ) : Boolean</div><div class='description'><div class='short'>Moves the file identified by this file object to another path. ...</div><div class='long'><p>Moves the file identified by this file object to another path.</p>\n\n<p><p>Note that this method moves the stored file, but doesn't update this \nfile object to point to the new path. To access the file after moving it,\nyou must call <a href=\"#!/api/Titanium.Filesystem-method-getFile\" rel=\"Titanium.Filesystem-method-getFile\" class=\"docClass\">getFile</a> using the destination\npath to obtain a new file handle.</p>\n\n</p><h3 class=\"pa\">Parameters</h3><ul><li><span class='pre'>newpath</span> : String<div class='sub-desc'><p>New location for the file.</p>\n\n</div></li></ul><h3 class='pa'>Returns</h3><ul><li><span class='pre'>Boolean</span><div class='sub-desc'>\n</div></li></ul></div></div></div><div id='method-open' class='member  not-inherited'><a href='#' class='side expandable'><span>&nbsp;</span></a><div class='title'><div class='meta'><span class='defined-in' rel='Titanium.Filesystem.File'>Titanium.Filesystem.File</span></div><a href='#!/api/Titanium.Filesystem.File-method-open' class='name expandable'>open</a>( <span class='pre'>mode</span> ) : <a href=\"#!/api/Titanium.Filesystem.FileStream\" rel=\"Titanium.Filesystem.FileStream\" class=\"docClass\">Titanium.Filesystem.FileStream</a></div><div class='description'><div class='short'>Opens the file identified by this file object for random access. ...</div><div class='long'><p>Opens the file identified by this file object for random access.</p>\n\n<p><p>You can open the file for reading, writing, or appending by specifying one of the \n<code>MODE</code> constants from <a href=\"#!/api/Titanium.Filesystem\" rel=\"Titanium.Filesystem\" class=\"docClass\">Titanium.Filesystem</a>:\n<a href=\"#!/api/Titanium.Filesystem-property-MODE_READ\" rel=\"Titanium.Filesystem-property-MODE_READ\" class=\"docClass\">MODE_READ</a>, <a href=\"#!/api/Titanium.Filesystem-property-MODE_WRITE\" rel=\"Titanium.Filesystem-property-MODE_WRITE\" class=\"docClass\">MODE_WRITE</a>, \nor <a href=\"#!/api/Titanium.Filesystem-property-MODE_APPEND\" rel=\"Titanium.Filesystem-property-MODE_APPEND\" class=\"docClass\">MODE_APPEND</a>.</p>\n\n\n\n\n<p>The <code>FileStream</code> object returned by this call can be used to read from, write to, or \nappend to the file, depending on what mode the file is opened in.</p>\n\n</p><h3 class=\"pa\">Parameters</h3><ul><li><span class='pre'>mode</span> : Number<div class='sub-desc'><p>Mode to open the file in: <code>MODE_READ</code>, <code>MODE_WRITE</code>, or <code>MODE_APPEND</code>.</p>\n\n</div></li></ul><h3 class='pa'>Returns</h3><ul><li><span class='pre'><a href=\"#!/api/Titanium.Filesystem.FileStream\" rel=\"Titanium.Filesystem.FileStream\" class=\"docClass\">Titanium.Filesystem.FileStream</a></span><div class='sub-desc'>\n</div></li></ul></div></div></div><div id='method-read' class='member  not-inherited'><a href='#' class='side expandable'><span>&nbsp;</span></a><div class='title'><div class='meta'><span class='defined-in' rel='Titanium.Filesystem.File'>Titanium.Filesystem.File</span></div><a href='#!/api/Titanium.Filesystem.File-method-read' class='name expandable'>read</a>( <span class='pre'></span> ) : <a href=\"#!/api/Titanium.Blob\" rel=\"Titanium.Blob\" class=\"docClass\">Titanium.Blob</a></div><div class='description'><div class='short'>Returns the contents of the file identified by this file object as a Blob. ...</div><div class='long'><p>Returns the contents of the file identified by this file object as a <code>Blob</code>.</p>\n\n<h3 class='pa'>Returns</h3><ul><li><span class='pre'><a href=\"#!/api/Titanium.Blob\" rel=\"Titanium.Blob\" class=\"docClass\">Titanium.Blob</a></span><div class='sub-desc'>\n</div></li></ul></div></div></div><div id='method-removeEventListener' class='member  inherited'><a href='#' class='side expandable'><span>&nbsp;</span></a><div class='title'><div class='meta'><a href='#!/api/Titanium.Proxy' rel='Titanium.Proxy' class='defined-in docClass'>Titanium.Proxy</a></div><a href='#!/api/Titanium.Proxy-method-removeEventListener' class='name expandable'>removeEventListener</a>( <span class='pre'>name, callback</span> )</div><div class='description'><div class='short'>Removes the specified callback as an event listener for the named event. ...</div><div class='long'><p>Removes the specified callback as an event listener for the named event.</p>\n\n<p><p>Multiple listeners can be registered for the same event, so the \n<code>callback</code> parameter is used to determine which listener to remove. </p>\n\n\n\n\n<p>When adding a listener, you must save a reference to the callback function\nin order to remove the listener later:</p>\n\n\n\n\n<pre><code>var listener = function() { Ti.API.info(\"Event listener called.\"); }\nwindow.addEventListener('click', listener);\n</code></pre>\n\n\n\n\n<p>To remove the listener, pass in a reference to the callback function:</p>\n\n\n\n\n<pre><code>window.removeEventListener('click', listener);\n</code></pre>\n\n</p><h3 class=\"pa\">Parameters</h3><ul><li><span class='pre'>name</span> : String<div class='sub-desc'><p>Name of the event.</p>\n\n</div></li><li><span class='pre'>callback</span> : Callback&lt;Object&gt;<div class='sub-desc'><p>Callback function to remove. Must be the same function passed to <code>addEventListener</code>.</p>\n\n</div></li></ul><h3 class='pa'>Returns</h3><ul><li><span class='pre'>void</span></li></ul></div></div></div><div id='method-rename' class='member  not-inherited'><a href='#' class='side expandable'><span>&nbsp;</span></a><div class='title'><div class='meta'><span class='defined-in' rel='Titanium.Filesystem.File'>Titanium.Filesystem.File</span></div><a href='#!/api/Titanium.Filesystem.File-method-rename' class='name expandable'>rename</a>( <span class='pre'>newname</span> ) : Boolean</div><div class='description'><div class='short'>Renames the file identified by this file object. ...</div><div class='long'><p>Renames the file identified by this file object.</p>\n\n<p><p>Returns <code>true</code> if the file was successfully renamed.</p>\n\n\n\n\n<p>Fails if the destination is in a different directory than the current file.\nUse <a href=\"#!/api/Titanium.Filesystem.File-method-move\" rel=\"Titanium.Filesystem.File-method-move\" class=\"docClass\">move</a> to move a file to a different directory.</p>\n\n\n\n\n<p>Note that this method renames the stored file, but doesn't update this \nfile object to point to the new path. To access the file after renaming it,\nyou must call <a href=\"#!/api/Titanium.Filesystem-method-getFile\" rel=\"Titanium.Filesystem-method-getFile\" class=\"docClass\">getFile</a> using the destination\npath to obtain a new file handle.</p>\n\n</p><h3 class=\"pa\">Parameters</h3><ul><li><span class='pre'>newname</span> : String<div class='sub-desc'><p>New name for the file.</p>\n\n</div></li></ul><h3 class='pa'>Returns</h3><ul><li><span class='pre'>Boolean</span><div class='sub-desc'>\n</div></li></ul></div></div></div><div id='method-resolve' class='member  not-inherited'><a href='#' class='side expandable'><span>&nbsp;</span></a><div class='title'><div class='meta'><span class='defined-in' rel='Titanium.Filesystem.File'>Titanium.Filesystem.File</span></div><a href='#!/api/Titanium.Filesystem.File-method-resolve' class='name expandable'>resolve</a>( <span class='pre'></span> ) : String</div><div class='description'><div class='short'>Returns the fully-resolved native path associated with this file object. ...</div><div class='long'><p>Returns the fully-resolved native path associated with this file object.</p>\n\n<p><p>On iOS, the path returned by this method is a plain file path, not a URL. It is suitable\nfor use in native modules that need to access the file using native APIs.</p>\n\n\n\n\n<p>On Android, the return value of <code>resolve</code> is a <code>file://</code> URL, identical to the\n<a href=\"#!/api/Titanium.Filesystem.File-property-nativePath\" rel=\"Titanium.Filesystem.File-property-nativePath\" class=\"docClass\">nativePath</a> property.</p>\n\n</p><h3 class='pa'>Returns</h3><ul><li><span class='pre'>String</span><div class='sub-desc'>\n</div></li></ul></div></div></div><div id='method-setBubbleParent' class='member  inherited'><a href='#' class='side expandable'><span>&nbsp;</span></a><div class='title'><div class='meta'><a href='#!/api/Titanium.Proxy' rel='Titanium.Proxy' class='defined-in docClass'>Titanium.Proxy</a></div><a href='#!/api/Titanium.Proxy-method-setBubbleParent' class='name expandable'>setBubbleParent</a>( <span class='pre'>bubbleParent</span> )</div><div class='description'><div class='short'>Sets the value of the bubbleParent property. ...</div><div class='long'><p>Sets the value of the <a href=\"#!/api/Titanium.Proxy-property-bubbleParent\" rel=\"Titanium.Proxy-property-bubbleParent\" class=\"docClass\">bubbleParent</a> property.</p>\n\n<ul class='platforms'><li class='platform-android'\n        title='Android'>3.0.0</li><li class='platform-iphone'\n        title='iPhone'>3.0.0</li><li class='platform-ipad'\n        title='iPad'>3.0.0</li><li class='platform-windowsphone'\n        title='Window Phone'>4.1.0</li></ul><h3 class=\"pa\">Parameters</h3><ul><li><span class='pre'>bubbleParent</span> : Boolean<div class='sub-desc'><p>New value for the property.</p>\n\n</div></li></ul><h3 class='pa'>Returns</h3><ul><li><span class='pre'>void</span></li></ul></div></div></div><div id='method-setHidden' class='member  not-inherited'><a href='#' class='side expandable'><span>&nbsp;</span></a><div class='title'><div class='meta'><span class='defined-in' rel='Titanium.Filesystem.File'>Titanium.Filesystem.File</span></div><a href='#!/api/Titanium.Filesystem.File-method-setHidden' class='name expandable'>setHidden</a>( <span class='pre'>hidden</span> )</div><div class='description'><div class='short'>Sets the value of the hidden property. ...</div><div class='long'><p>Sets the value of the <a href=\"#!/api/Titanium.Filesystem.File-property-hidden\" rel=\"Titanium.Filesystem.File-property-hidden\" class=\"docClass\">hidden</a> property.</p>\n\n<h3 class=\"pa\">Parameters</h3><ul><li><span class='pre'>hidden</span> : Boolean<div class='sub-desc'><p>New value for the property.</p>\n\n</div></li></ul><h3 class='pa'>Returns</h3><ul><li><span class='pre'>void</span></li></ul></div></div></div><div id='method-setLifecycleContainer' class='member  inherited'><a href='#' class='side expandable'><span>&nbsp;</span></a><div class='title'><div class='meta'><a href='#!/api/Titanium.Proxy' rel='Titanium.Proxy' class='defined-in docClass'>Titanium.Proxy</a></div><a href='#!/api/Titanium.Proxy-method-setLifecycleContainer' class='name expandable'>setLifecycleContainer</a>( <span class='pre'>lifecycleContainer</span> )</div><div class='description'><div class='short'>Sets the value of the lifecycleContainer property. ...</div><div class='long'><p>Sets the value of the <a href=\"#!/api/Titanium.Proxy-property-lifecycleContainer\" rel=\"Titanium.Proxy-property-lifecycleContainer\" class=\"docClass\">lifecycleContainer</a> property.</p>\n\n<ul class='platforms'><li class='platform-android'\n        title='Android'>3.6.0</li><li class='platform-windowsphone'\n        title='Window Phone'>4.1.0</li></ul><h3 class=\"pa\">Parameters</h3><ul><li><span class='pre'>lifecycleContainer</span> : <a href=\"#!/api/Titanium.UI.Window\" rel=\"Titanium.UI.Window\" class=\"docClass\">Titanium.UI.Window</a>/<a href=\"#!/api/Titanium.UI.TabGroup\" rel=\"Titanium.UI.TabGroup\" class=\"docClass\">Titanium.UI.TabGroup</a><div class='sub-desc'><p>New value for the property.</p>\n\n</div></li></ul><h3 class='pa'>Returns</h3><ul><li><span class='pre'>void</span></li></ul></div></div></div><div id='method-setProtectionKey' class='member  not-inherited'><a href='#' class='side expandable'><span>&nbsp;</span></a><div class='title'><div class='meta'><span class='defined-in' rel='Titanium.Filesystem.File'>Titanium.Filesystem.File</span></div><a href='#!/api/Titanium.Filesystem.File-method-setProtectionKey' class='name expandable'>setProtectionKey</a>( <span class='pre'>fileProtectionType</span> ) : Boolean</div><div class='description'><div class='short'>Sets the protection key as an attribute to the file identified by this file object. ...</div><div class='long'><p>Sets the protection key as an attribute to the file identified by this file object.</p>\n\n<p><p>Returns <code>true</code> if successfully set. Returns <code>false</code> if failed.</p>\n\n</p><ul class='platforms'><li class='platform-iphone'\n        title='iPhone'>4.1.0</li><li class='platform-ipad'\n        title='iPad'>4.1.0</li></ul><h3 class=\"pa\">Parameters</h3><ul><li><span class='pre'>fileProtectionType</span> : String<div class='sub-desc'><p>File protection type.</p>\n\n\n<p>This API can be assigned the following constants:<ul>\n <li> <a href=\"#!/api/Titanium.Filesystem-property-IOS_FILE_PROTECTION_NONE\" rel=\"Titanium.Filesystem-property-IOS_FILE_PROTECTION_NONE\" class=\"docClass\">Titanium.Filesystem.IOS_FILE_PROTECTION_NONE</a>\n <li> <a href=\"#!/api/Titanium.Filesystem-property-IOS_FILE_PROTECTION_COMPLETE\" rel=\"Titanium.Filesystem-property-IOS_FILE_PROTECTION_COMPLETE\" class=\"docClass\">Titanium.Filesystem.IOS_FILE_PROTECTION_COMPLETE</a>\n <li> <a href=\"#!/api/Titanium.Filesystem-property-IOS_FILE_PROTECTION_COMPLETE_UNLESS_OPEN\" rel=\"Titanium.Filesystem-property-IOS_FILE_PROTECTION_COMPLETE_UNLESS_OPEN\" class=\"docClass\">Titanium.Filesystem.IOS_FILE_PROTECTION_COMPLETE_UNLESS_OPEN</a>\n <li> <a href=\"#!/api/Titanium.Filesystem-property-IOS_FILE_PROTECTION_COMPLETE_UNTIL_FIRST_USER_AUTHENTICATION\" rel=\"Titanium.Filesystem-property-IOS_FILE_PROTECTION_COMPLETE_UNTIL_FIRST_USER_AUTHENTICATION\" class=\"docClass\">Titanium.Filesystem.IOS_FILE_PROTECTION_COMPLETE_UNTIL_FIRST_USER_AUTHENTICATION</a>\n</li></li></li></li></ul></p>\n\n</div></li></ul><h3 class='pa'>Returns</h3><ul><li><span class='pre'>Boolean</span><div class='sub-desc'>\n</div></li></ul></div></div></div><div id='method-setRemoteBackup' class='member  not-inherited'><a href='#' class='side expandable'><span>&nbsp;</span></a><div class='title'><div class='meta'><span class='defined-in' rel='Titanium.Filesystem.File'>Titanium.Filesystem.File</span></div><a href='#!/api/Titanium.Filesystem.File-method-setRemoteBackup' class='name expandable'>setRemoteBackup</a>( <span class='pre'>remoteBackup</span> )</div><div class='description'><div class='short'>Sets the value of the remoteBackup property. ...</div><div class='long'><p>Sets the value of the <a href=\"#!/api/Titanium.Filesystem.File-property-remoteBackup\" rel=\"Titanium.Filesystem.File-property-remoteBackup\" class=\"docClass\">remoteBackup</a> property.</p>\n\n<ul class='platforms'><li class='platform-iphone'\n        title='iPhone'>1.8.0</li><li class='platform-ipad'\n        title='iPad'>1.8.0</li></ul><h3 class=\"pa\">Parameters</h3><ul><li><span class='pre'>remoteBackup</span> : Boolean<div class='sub-desc'><p>New value for the property.</p>\n\n</div></li></ul><h3 class='pa'>Returns</h3><ul><li><span class='pre'>void</span></li></ul></div></div></div><div id='method-spaceAvailable' class='member  not-inherited'><a href='#' class='side expandable'><span>&nbsp;</span></a><div class='title'><div class='meta'><span class='defined-in' rel='Titanium.Filesystem.File'>Titanium.Filesystem.File</span></div><a href='#!/api/Titanium.Filesystem.File-method-spaceAvailable' class='name expandable'>spaceAvailable</a>( <span class='pre'></span> ) : Number</div><div class='description'><div class='short'>Returns the amount of free space available on the device where the file identified by this file object is stored. ...</div><div class='long'><p>Returns the amount of free space available on the device where the file identified by this file object is stored.</p>\n\n<p><p>Free space is returned in bytes.</p>\n\n</p><h3 class='pa'>Returns</h3><ul><li><span class='pre'>Number</span><div class='sub-desc'>\n</div></li></ul></div></div></div><div id='method-write' class='member  not-inherited'><a href='#' class='side expandable'><span>&nbsp;</span></a><div class='title'><div class='meta'><span class='defined-in' rel='Titanium.Filesystem.File'>Titanium.Filesystem.File</span></div><a href='#!/api/Titanium.Filesystem.File-method-write' class='name expandable'>write</a>( <span class='pre'>data, [append]</span> ) : Boolean</div><div class='description'><div class='short'>Writes the specified data to the file identified by this file object. ...</div><div class='long'><p>Writes the specified data to the file identified by this file object.</p>\n\n<p><p>If the <code>append</code> parameter is <code>false</code> or not specified, any existing data in \nthe file is overwritten. </p>\n\n\n\n\n<p>If <code>append</code> is <code>true</code>, the specified data is appended to the end of the file.</p>\n\n</p><h3 class=\"pa\">Parameters</h3><ul><li><span class='pre'>data</span> : String/<a href=\"#!/api/Titanium.Filesystem.File\" rel=\"Titanium.Filesystem.File\" class=\"docClass\">Titanium.Filesystem.File</a>/<a href=\"#!/api/Titanium.Blob\" rel=\"Titanium.Blob\" class=\"docClass\">Titanium.Blob</a><div class='sub-desc'><p>Data to write, as a String, <code>Blob</code> or <code>File</code> object.</p>\n\n</div></li><li><span class='pre'>append</span> : Boolean (optional)<div class='sub-desc'><p>If <code>true</code>, append the data to the end of the file.</p>\n\n</div></li></ul><h3 class='pa'>Returns</h3><ul><li><span class='pre'>Boolean</span><div class='sub-desc'>\n</div></li></ul></div></div></div></div></div></div></div>"});